        <briefdescription>
<para>Build a SigMF <computeroutput>.sigmf-meta</computeroutput> JSON document for a generated capture. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><computeroutput>global</computeroutput> carries core:datatype (from sample_type+endian, e.g. &quot;ci16_le&quot;), core:sample_rate, core:version &quot;1.0.0&quot;, and a wfmgen description/author. <computeroutput>captures</computeroutput> is a single capture at sample 0 / frequency <computeroutput>fc</computeroutput>. <computeroutput>annotations</computeroutput> has one entry per composer segment — sample span, frequency edges (fc + freq ± bandwidth/2, bandwidth ≈ fs/sps for symbol/chip types), a core:label of the waveform type, and custom <computeroutput>wfmgen:*</computeroutput> parameters.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="return"><para>malloc&apos;d JSON string (caller frees), or NULL on allocation failure. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
